HEADWORD: furnished
<hw>furnished</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>provided with necessary
furnishings; -- used especially of rented apartments having furniture
included in the rental price; <as>as, a <ex>furnished</ex>
apartment</as>. Opposite of <ant>unfurnished</ant>.</def> [Narrower
terms: <stype>stocked, stocked with </stype>; <stype>appointed</stype>;
<stype>well-appointed, well-found </stype>; <stype>fitted out, outfitted
</stype>]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> equipped.</syn>⟦br⟧
